by foot. One thing this Viking land does well is grocery shopping! Everyone shop at the same big grocery chain, COOP up the road from where I live. Compared to American grocery stores, this one is great: every city has one, they are always super clean, have a great selection (really a worldwide selection), stocked with servers, have huge parking lots, all price any Canadian or American store, and the prices are low. Like...coop or Safeway low.

Mixing with new friends, not all of them human.

Before I introduce you to the new friends I am meeting, Russell needs me to let you know we already had friends here in Norway (proud shout out to one of my favourite Njård friends:) Big thanks Jorid!!)) The above picture is a cold feeling cold I experienced while meeting Lærke in Vinterhage. Thank you Lærke for the fun of hanging outside and learning about ClubLogic + Hypo-Fruta-Canastell.

It's Norway, the cold is real!!! Below, Russell and I are both jumped up in order to meet the deer in the street that is looking somewhat perturbed.

The best way to meet new friends, ocean friendly, is by boat on Glasir or in a UNESCO heritage park. I will let the pictures speak for themselves...though as promised this blog will be filled with other bits from my everyday #WorkingFromNorway life.

Welcoming, Fun Huset
